arXiv:2404.11632v1 Announce Type: new Abstract: We show that the Raychaudhuri equation remains invariant for certain solutions of scalar fields $\phi$ whose Lagrangian is non-canonical and of the form $\mathcal{L}(X,\phi)=-V(\phi)F(X)$, with $X= rac{1}{2} g_{\mu
u} 
abla^{\mu}\phi 
abla^{
u} \phi$, $V(\phi)$ the potential. Solutions exist for both homogeneous and inhomogeneous fields and are reminiscent of inflaton scenarios.
